    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <div1 type="letter">
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03180.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1888-02-03"><hi rend="underline">Feb. 3 '88</hi><ptr target="loc.03180_n1"/></date>
                </dateline> 
            </opener> 
            <p>—The little head in oil, with hat (of Elias Hicks<ptr target="n4265"/>) sent me from Richmond
                Indiana painted by Sidney Morse<ptr target="duk.00863_n3"/>—As I understand it is from a photo, or daguerreotype of Elias, from life, taken about
                1828 or '29 there.<ptr target="loc.03180_n2"/></p>
        </div1>   
            <!-- The following enclosure, copied by Whitman, is pasted on the letter -->
        <div1 type="enclosure">
            <addSpan spanTo="#a01" rend="pasteon" xml:id="add1"/>
                        <floatingText rend="flat"> 
                     <body> 
                   <opener> 
                       <note type="authorial">Morse's letter</note>
                       <name type="place">Richmond Indiana</name>
                        <dateline>
                           <date when="1888-01-31">January 31, 1888</date>
                       </dateline> 
                   </opener>
                        <p><handShift rend="manuscript"/>..."a little sketch
                        in oil (on a box cover) from an old photo of a steel engraving brought me by
                        a Mr. Harris<ptr target="n5001"/> who heard Elias preach when he was 10 years old. He says my
                        copy [this picture] is quite as good as the original. I don't think so
                        myself; but it approximates."<ptr target="loc.03180_n3"/></p>
                     </body>
                     </floatingText>
            <anchor xml:id="a01"/>
        </div1>
